By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  Three states – Lagos, FCT and Plateau accounted for 53.9 percent of the 453 new cases of COVID-19 infections recorded in Nigeria on Wednesday, the report of the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has revealed. These three states recorded 113, 72 and 59 new cases respectively. The other 13 states accounted for the remaining 46.1 percent of the COVID-19 patients that tested positive for the novel virus pandemic which was first recorded in Nigeria on the 27th of February 2020. According to the NCDC’s report released via its twitter handle late Wednesday night, the total confirmed cases  is now 47,743 out of which a total of 33,943 patients have been treated and released. The report added that 956 patients have died  of the COVID-19 related complications in Nigeria. The released reports are as follow: Lagos-113 FCT-72 Plateau-59 Enugu-55 Kaduna-38 Ondo-32 Osun-26 Ebonyi-20 Ogun-9 Delta-8 Borno-7 Akwa Ibom-6 Oyo-5 Bauchi-1 Kano-1 Ekiti-1 47,743 confirmed; 33,943 discharged and  956 deaths. State by state breakdown :  By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has announced the confirmation of 453 new cases of COVID-19 infections just as it reported that a total of 33,044 patients have been treated and discharged in Nigeria since the index case in February 27, 2020. Disclosing… August 9, 2020 In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Health agency in charge of COVID-19 in Nigeria said that 290 new cases of COVID-19 have been recorded, bringing the total confirmed cases to  46,867 in the country. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control also said that it has also recorded five… August 11, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Thursday said that it has confirmed 354 new cases of COVID-19 infection, bringing the total confirmed cases to 45,244. The health agency reported that the 354 new infections were re